<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-14T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-14T20:00:00-05:00" n="1389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1389">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/232.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-14T18:00:00-07:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1914, 6 pm.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I received information today from Torreon that Villa issued orders
                                that no Spanish property be touched until he personally gave orders.
                                Carranza will probably go to Torreon to see Villa instead of Villa
                                going to Chihuahua as Villa’s presence is necessary at the
                                front.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>